<taxonomicName id="4C4B25A2272FFF9EFD9AFE8099BDFE5A" authorityName="Matschie" authorityYear="1916" box="[547,721,375,401]" class="Mammalia" family="Didelphidae" genus="Monodelphiops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Didelphimorphia" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93F8233272FFF9EFD9AFE8099BDFE5A" box="[547,721,375,401]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Monodelphiops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with other subgenera of 
<taxonomicName id="4C4B25A2272FFF9EFC40FE809FE0FE5A" authorityName="Burnett" authorityYear="1830" box="[1017,1164,375,401]" class="Mammalia" family="Didelphidae" genus="Monodelphis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Didelphimorphia" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93F8233272FFF9EFC40FE809FE0FE5A" box="[1017,1164,375,401]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Monodelphis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have already been provided (see above).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3510DAA272FFF9EFF11FE369A0BFA6C" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BF45E21272FFF9EFF11FE369930FC9A" blockId="29.[120,1226,225,1447]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
REMARKS: Molecular sequence data are currently unavailable from 
<taxonomicName id="4C4B25A2272FFF9EFC0EFE369FADFE10" baseAuthorityName="Wagner" baseAuthorityYear="1842" box="[951,1217,449,475]" class="Mammalia" family="Didelphidae" genus="Monodelphis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Didelphimorphia" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="unistriata">
<emphasis id="B93F8233272FFF9EFC0EFE369FADFE10" box="[951,1217,449,475]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Monodelphis unistriata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, so inferences about its relationships are necessarily based on morphology. Although 
<bibRefCitation id="EFDA23D0272FFF9EFBECFE109BA9FDED" author="Pine, R. H. &amp; D. A. Flores &amp; K. Bauer" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" pagination="425 - 441" refId="ref17031" refString="Pine, R. H., D. A. Flores, and K. Bauer. 2013. The second known specimen of Monodelphis unistriata (Wagner) (Mammalia: Didelphimorphia), with redescription of the species and phylogenetic analysis. Zootaxa 3: 425 - 441." type="journal article" year="2013">Pine et al. (2013)</bibRefCitation>
recovered 
<taxonomicName id="4C4B25A2272FFF9EFEF1FDFA9A8DFDED" baseAuthorityName="Wagner" baseAuthorityYear="1842" box="[328,481,525,550]" class="Mammalia" family="Didelphidae" genus="Monodelphis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Didelphimorphia" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="unistriata">
<emphasis id="B93F8233272FFF9EFEF1FDFA9A8DFDED" box="[328,481,525,550]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">M. unistriata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as the sister taxon of 
<taxonomicName id="4C4B25A2272FFF9EFD5BFDFA9808FDED" authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1888" box="[738,868,524,550]" class="Mammalia" family="Didelphidae" genus="Microdelphys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Didelphimorphia" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="iheringi">
<emphasis id="B93F8233272FFF9EFD5BFDFA9808FDED" box="[738,868,524,550]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">M. iheringi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on a combined analysis of morphological characters and cytochrome- 
<emphasis id="B93F8233272FFF9EFD2EFDC699C9FD80" box="[663,677,561,587]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">b</emphasis>
sequences (the latter coded as missing for 
<taxonomicName id="4C4B25A2272FFF9EFB10FDC59B85FDBB" baseAuthorityName="Wagner" baseAuthorityYear="1842" class="Mammalia" family="Didelphidae" genus="Monodelphis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Didelphimorphia" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="unistriata">
<emphasis id="B93F8233272FFF9EFB10FDC59B85FDBB" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">M. unistriata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), the authors themselves stated that the characters sampled for their study were not “sufficiently informative as to allow refined elucidation of the relationships in this genus” (
<bibRefCitation id="EFDA23D0272FFF9EFB2AFD8B9A58FD70" author="Pine, R. H. &amp; D. A. Flores &amp; K. Bauer" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" pagination="425 - 441" refId="ref17031" refString="Pine, R. H., D. A. Flores, and K. Bauer. 2013. The second known specimen of Monodelphis unistriata (Wagner) (Mammalia: Didelphimorphia), with redescription of the species and phylogenetic analysis. Zootaxa 3: 425 - 441." type="journal article" year="2013">Pine et al., 2013: 433</bibRefCitation>
), and that additional characters as well as inclusion of other species would be necessary to “ever more firmly ascertain the relationships of this enigmatic taxon” (
<bibRefCitation id="EFDA23D0272FFF9EFBF5FD309B83FCCC" author="Pine, R. H. &amp; D. A. Flores &amp; K. Bauer" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" pagination="425 - 441" refId="ref17031" refString="Pine, R. H., D. A. Flores, and K. Bauer. 2013. The second known specimen of Monodelphis unistriata (Wagner) (Mammalia: Didelphimorphia), with redescription of the species and phylogenetic analysis. Zootaxa 3: 425 - 441." type="journal article" year="2013">Pine et al., 2013: 435</bibRefCitation>
). They also noted multiple morphological similarities between 
<taxonomicName id="4C4B25A2272FFF9EFC6DFD1A9F02FCCD" baseAuthorityName="Wagner" baseAuthorityYear="1842" box="[980,1134,749,774]" class="Mammalia" family="Didelphidae" genus="Monodelphis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Didelphimorphia" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="unistriata">
<emphasis id="B93F8233272FFF9EFC6DFD1A9F02FCCD" box="[980,1134,749,774]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">M. unistriata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C4B25A2272FFF9EFB11FD1A9B84FCE0" authorityName="Wagner" authorityYear="1847" class="Mammalia" family="Didelphidae" genus="Monodelphis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Didelphimorphia" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="dimidiata">
<emphasis id="B93F8233272FFF9EFB11FD1A9B84FCE0" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">M. dimidiata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, suggesting that 
<taxonomicName id="4C4B25A2272FFF9EFE08FCE59927FCE0" baseAuthorityName="Wagner" baseAuthorityYear="1842" box="[433,587,786,811]" class="Mammalia" family="Didelphidae" genus="Monodelphis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Didelphimorphia" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="unistriata">
<emphasis id="B93F8233272FFF9EFE08FCE59927FCE0" box="[433,587,786,811]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">M. unistriata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
could be more closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="4C4B25A2272FFF9EFC6DFCE59F00FCE0" authorityName="Wagner" authorityYear="1847" box="[980,1132,785,811]" class="Mammalia" family="Didelphidae" genus="Monodelphis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Didelphimorphia" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="dimidiata">
<emphasis id="B93F8233272FFF9EFC6DFCE59F00FCE0" box="[980,1132,785,811]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">M. dimidiata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
than to any other species (
<bibRefCitation id="EFDA23D0272FFF9EFEEDFCC09923FC9A" author="Pine, R. H. &amp; D. A. Flores &amp; K. Bauer" box="[340,591,823,849]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" pagination="425 - 441" refId="ref17031" refString="Pine, R. H., D. A. Flores, and K. Bauer. 2013. The second known specimen of Monodelphis unistriata (Wagner) (Mammalia: Didelphimorphia), with redescription of the species and phylogenetic analysis. Zootaxa 3: 425 - 441." type="journal article" year="2013">Pine et al., 2013: 432</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF45E21272FFF9EFF10FCAB9AC6FADA" blockId="29.[120,1226,225,1447]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
Among several possible explanations for such anomalous results, 
<taxonomicName id="4C4B25A2272FFF9EFC00FCAA9F38FCBD" baseAuthorityName="Wagner" baseAuthorityYear="1842" box="[953,1108,861,886]" class="Mammalia" family="Didelphidae" genus="Monodelphis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Didelphimorphia" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="unistriata">
<emphasis id="B93F8233272FFF9EFC00FCAA9F38FCBD" box="[953,1108,861,886]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">M. unistriata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known from just two specimens, one consisting only of a skin and the other of a skin and part of the skull (
<bibRefCitation id="EFDA23D0272FFF9EFF48FC509AD5FC0A" author="Pine, R. H. &amp; D. A. Flores &amp; K. Bauer" box="[241,441,935,961]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" pagination="425 - 441" refId="ref17031" refString="Pine, R. H., D. A. Flores, and K. Bauer. 2013. The second known specimen of Monodelphis unistriata (Wagner) (Mammalia: Didelphimorphia), with redescription of the species and phylogenetic analysis. Zootaxa 3: 425 - 441." type="journal article" year="2013">Pine et al., 2013</bibRefCitation>
: 
<figureCitation id="137042A4272FFF9EFE7CFC509968FC0A" box="[453,516,935,961]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="6.[120,162,1701,1722]" captionTargetBox="[161,1197,230,1664]" captionTargetId="figure-12@6.[120,1224,224,1674]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIG. 2. Ventral views of skins with alternative pelage markings (see text): A, Monodelphis handleyi (MUSM 23810); B, M. glirina (MVZ 197456); C, M. touan (USNM 549280). Scale bar = 50 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4598438" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4598438/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">fig. 2</figureCitation>
), so information is missing for many morphological characters, including those of the posterior braincase, zygomatic arches, and ear region. We hypothesize that 
<taxonomicName id="4C4B25A2272FFF9EFEF3FC059A84FBC0" baseAuthorityName="Wagner" baseAuthorityYear="1842" box="[330,488,1010,1035]" class="Mammalia" family="Didelphidae" genus="Monodelphis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Didelphimorphia" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="unistriata">
<emphasis id="B93F8233272FFF9EFEF3FC059A84FBC0" box="[330,488,1010,1035]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">M. unistriata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C4B25A2272FFF9EFD93FC0599ABFBC0" authorityName="Wagner" authorityYear="1847" box="[554,711,1009,1035]" class="Mammalia" family="Didelphidae" genus="Monodelphis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Didelphimorphia" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="dimidiata">
<emphasis id="B93F8233272FFF9EFD93FC0599ABFBC0" box="[554,711,1009,1035]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">M. dimidiata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are sister taxa based on shared attributes that seem likely to optimize as synapomorphies in future phylogenetic analyses. Such attributes include: a dorsal body pelage with a grizzled middorsum contrasting with clear yellowish, orange, or reddish flanks; large tail scales arranged in spiral series; very short incisive foramina (a striking similarity previously noted by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFDA23D0272FFF9EFD59FB7098CFFB6A" author="Pine, R. H. &amp; D. A. Flores &amp; K. Bauer" box="[736,931,1159,1185]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" pagination="425 - 441" refId="ref17031" refString="Pine, R. H., D. A. Flores, and K. Bauer. 2013. The second known specimen of Monodelphis unistriata (Wagner) (Mammalia: Didelphimorphia), with redescription of the species and phylogenetic analysis. Zootaxa 3: 425 - 441." type="journal article" year="2013">Pine et al., 2013</bibRefCitation>
); and short maxillopalatine fenestrae. Of course, this hypothesis needs to be tested using taxon-dense phylogenetic analyses of morphological and molecular data when fresh material of this apparently elusive species become available.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF45E21272FFF9EFF11FAEB9A0BFA6C" blockId="29.[120,1226,225,1447]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
NOTES ON DISTRIBUTION AND SYMPATRY: 
